@renatobecker We are already using the method [here](https://github.com/RocketChat/Rocket.Chat/pull/21285/files#diff-7ea22d1f2dc14b7eb09df59074efe4d9a43c96cce7e9008e92e9b792fe13c56cR196)

The issue is that when the Client is calling server to get this info over [here](https://github.com/RocketChat/Rocket.Chat/pull/21285/files#diff-3cb80e6d6d29b75c26f675e0c04a803fc66185b5b021515737836005c2c3e76fR87), its not saving the `routeConfig` property into the context, due to which we aren't able to access this property over [here](https://github.com/RocketChat/Rocket.Chat/pull/21285/files#diff-7ea22d1f2dc14b7eb09df59074efe4d9a43c96cce7e9008e92e9b792fe13c56cR201)

Hence the above change is required. You can try testing this in action, by removing the above line and then notice the `omnichannelRouteConfig` property [here](https://github.com/RocketChat/Rocket.Chat/pull/21285/files#diff-7ea22d1f2dc14b7eb09df59074efe4d9a43c96cce7e9008e92e9b792fe13c56cR201). You'll notice that `undefined` there
